                    <ab><title>Exodus 31</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l>And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <l n="2">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             ‘See, I have called by name Bezalel, son of Uri, son
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             of Hur, of the tribe of Judah.</l>
                        <l n="3">And I have filled him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             with the spirit of God, with wisdom and with reason and with knowledge
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and with every kind of work,</l>
                        <l n="4">To make patterns, to work in gold
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             and in silver and in bronze,</l>
                        <l n="5">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             to fill with a mason, and to do all kind of work with a woodworker</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="6">And I: lo, I have given with him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             Oholiab, son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             I have put wisdom in the hearts of all that are wise hearted. And that
                            they shall make
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             all that I have commanded you:</l>
                        <l n="7">The tent of meeting,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and the ark of the law, and the cover that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             is on it, and all the equipment of the tent,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="8">And the table and its equipment, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             the pure lampstand and all its equipment, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             altar of incense,</l>
                        <l n="9">And the altar
                            <milestone unit="page" n="139v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             of burnt offering and all its equipment, and the basin and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             its place,</l>
                        <l n="10">And the colourful garments,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and the holy garments for Aaron, the priest, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             garments of his sons, for their service as priests,</l>
                        <l n="11">And the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             anointing oil, and the fragrant incense for the Holy.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             They shall do everything as I have commanded you.’</l>
                        <l n="12">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             the Lord said to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <l n="13">‘And you shall speak
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             to the children of Israel, saying, “Just: you shall keep my Sabbaths,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             because it is a sign between me and you throughout your generations: to
                            know
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             that I am the Lord who sanctifies you.</l>
                        <l n="14">And you shall keep
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             the Sabbath, because it is holy to you. One who defiles it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             shall surely be put to death. Because anyone who does any work on it:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             that soul shall be cut off from among his people.</l>
                        <l n="15">Six
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             days work shall be done, and on the seventh day is the Sabbath, a day
                            of complete rest,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             holy to the Lord. Anyone who does any work on the Sabbath day
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             shall surely be put to death.</l>
                        <l n="16">And the children of Israel shall keep
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             the Sabbath, to consider the Sabbath holy
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             throughout their generations, an eternal covenant.</l>
                        <l n="17">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             It is a sign between me and the children of Israel forever, because in
                            six
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             days the Lord created the skies
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             and the earth, and on the seventh day he rested and relaxed.”’</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="140r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="18">And when he finished speaking with
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             him on Mount Sinai, he gave the two tablets of law to Moses, tablets of
                            stone,
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex031-P140r-L3_trl" n="3"
                                next="ADub.III.73.002.032.trl.xml#Ex032-P140r-L3_trl" />
                             written by the command of God. </l>
                    </ab>
